{"session_id": 51, "bill_id": 16426, "bill_type": "House Bill", "bill_number": 1120, "bill_title": "allow a medical necessity to be used as a defense in certain cases involving the possession or use of marijuana.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 2558, "is_prime": true}], "keywords": ["Marijuana"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2001-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2001/hju13hb1120a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2001-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2001/hju13hb1120a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2001-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2001/hju13hb1120a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2001-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2001/hju13hb1120a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2001-01-26T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2001/hju13hb1120a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2001-02-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2001/hju18hb1120a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 16426, "bill_version_id": 88229, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2001-01-23T08:15:47-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow a medical necessity to be used as a defense in certain cases involving the possession or use of marijuana. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. Any person arrested or prosecuted for the possession or use of marijuana may submit as a defense, a medical necessity, if: (1) The person has a medical condition recognized by a competent medical authority as a condition for which marijuana is a palliative; or (2) The person has a recommendation by a competent medical authority for the use of marijuana for a medical condition. Section 2. A medical necessity defense pursuant to this Act may, at the discretion of the accused, include: (1) Expert testimony; (2) A recommendation by a competent medical authority; and (3) Testimony by other persons with a similar medical condition. 450 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.021 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 16426, "action_date": "2001-01-23T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 88296, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/88296.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 154, "committee_id_action": 712, "committee_id_assigned": 710, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 16426, "action_date": "2001-01-26T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 88681, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/88681.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 710, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 16426, "action_date": "2001-01-26T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 88681, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/88681.pdf", "status_text": "Deferred to another day", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 710, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 16426, "action_date": "2001-01-26T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 88681, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/88681.pdf", "status_text": "Deferred to another day", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 710, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 16426, "action_date": "2001-02-02T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 89245, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/892